name: .AC$ File Extension
summary: Learn about .AC$ files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: Temporary file generated by AutoCAD, a 2D/3D drawing and design program; contains information used by various commands, including "UNDO" and "HIDDEN LINES."

content: AC$ files do not contain any drawing data and only exist when AutoCAD is open. They are automatically deleted when the program is closed.
